-- CFTC working to protect Lehman customers
-- 
-- Sun Sep 14, 2008 10:13pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/15/us-lehman-cftc-idUSWAT01004820080915

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - U.S. commodity regulators are working with global regulators to ensure that customers of Lehman Brothers' futures commission merchant are protected, the Commodity Futures Trading Commission said on Sunday. 

 Acting CFTC Chairman Walter Lukken also said the commission has been taking steps to maintain the stability and orderliness of the commodity futures and options markets. (Reporting by  Rachelle Younglai )